<br>
Temperance: 48 AC, 800 hp.<br>
<br>
Bulwark of Faith: 37 AC<br>
Symbol of Marzin: 640 HP + <br>
Heroic Bond: 360hp + , 18-19 AC<br>
Net: at least 55AC,  1000hp<br>
<br>
So ... Up to you. Temperance lasts longer and only takes up one buff slot, which is important at times too.<br>
<br>
At level 58, what I usually do is keep Heroic Bond and Naltron's Mark up (both group spells) and I upgrade the main tank and the crowd control with Symbol of Marzin and Bulwark of Faith. Net result only costs 3 peridots, as opposed to 6 for a full group. It takes the same amount of castings, too, as passing around Temperance to a full group.<br>
<br>
I also have Spellcasting Reinforcement II, so if I cast one round of Marzin/Heroic Bond/Bulwark, it's usually good for one dungeon encounter or a fair chunk of raid time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hendaddy>Hendaddy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/5/03 7:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC/HP buffs at 58</span><hr size=1> Thanks, exactly what i was looking for.  Thanks a bunch Elhana. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fayrnn>Fayrnn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>When in doubt and Hell <br>overruns your ranks,<br>
